# TypeScript Rules

## File Patterns

- **/*.ts
- **/*.tsx

## Code Style and Structure

- Always use ES module syntax
- Maintain consistent naming conventions
- Focus on writing correct, best practice, DRY code
- Use early returns to avoid nested conditions and improve readability
- Use constants instead of functions where possible
- Use descriptive names for variables and functions
- Use custom error types when appropriate
- Favor named exports over default exports
- Use efficient data structures
- Use efficient algorithms
- Keep performance in mind but do not over-optimize at the cost of readability
- Write code that is easy to test and maintain
- Write comprehensive tests for all new features
- Document code with JSDoc comments
- Do not remove any existing code unless necessary
- Do not remove my comments or commented-out code unless necessary
- Use lowercase in single line comments

## TypeScript Guidelines

- Use type inference where possible
- Avoid enums, use const enums when necessary
- Do not define function return types unless necessary
- Prefer types over interfaces
- Use proper type annotations
- Prefer `unknown` type over `any`
- Follow the project's TypeScript patterns
